\b \cf0 General Rules of Etiquette
\b0 \
\
\pard\tx220\tx720\tx1440\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\li720\fi-720\sl288\slmult1\pardirnatural
\ls2\ilvl0\cf0 {\listtext	\'95	}Never punish your child for a fault to which you are addicted yourself.\
{\listtext	\'95	}Never, when traveling abroad, be over-boastful in praise of your own country.\
{\listtext	\'95	}Never lend an article you have borrowed unless you have permission to do so\
{\listtext	\'95	}Never exhibit anger, impatience, or excitement when an accident happens.\
{\listtext	\'95	}Never will a gentleman allude to conquest which he may have made with ladies.\
{\listtext	\'95	}Never fail to offer the easiest and best seat in the room to an invalid, an elderly person, or a lady.}